	<text>
		<body>
			<p>From: Consul <persName ref="#ehri_dr_yukio_toyohara">Toyohara Yukio</persName> (<placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2035836/manzhouli.html">Manzhouli</placeName>)</p>
			<p>To: Ambassador <persName ref="#ehri_dr_umezu_yoshijirō">Umezu Yoshijirō</persName> (<placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/1837029/shinkyo-ri.html">Shinkyō</placeName>)</p>
			<p>CC: <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/institutions/jp-005465">MOFA Tokyo</term></p>
			<p>Re: Situation of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-642" type="subject">Persecution of Jews</term> in
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Germany</placeName></p>
			<p>Information gathered by the Foreign Affairs Section here for your reference. </p>
			<list type="ol" rend="1">
				<item> General Situation </item>
			</list>
			<p rend="margin noindent"> Due to the outbreak of second great war in Europe the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-642" type="subject">persecution of Jews</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Germany</placeName> has become intensified recently. At
				last the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> feel their <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-809" type="subject">living</term> to be under <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-662" type="subject">threat</term> and have no choice but to seek <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">refuge</term> abroad. </p>
			<list type="ol" rend="1">
				<item>
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-687" type="subject">Testimonies</term>
				</item>
			</list>
			<p rend="margin noindent"> Main <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-687" type="subject">testimonies</term> are
				as follows </p>
			<list type="ol" rend="a">
				<item>Due to the clandestine <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-195" type="subject">collaboration</term> of
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> living in <placeName
						ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Germany</placeName> and those in other countries,
						<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Germany</placeName> ended up losing the
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1049" type="subject">economic warfare</term> during the first
					great war in Europe. In view of this, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1032" type="subject"
						>authorities</term> are trying to avoid a repetition of such a scenario by driving them out of the country. However, there are
					about two million <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> in the country,
					and many occupy important places in society. Therefore, it is not easy to expel them. However, without expulsion, it will be
					difficult to ensure Germany’s <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-918" type="subject">economy</term> in
					a long-term war. In my view, to make them leave <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html"
						>Germany</placeName> voluntarily, [the authorities] are using methods such as denying them jobs and making their life
					extremely <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-615" type="subject">restricted</term> so as to expect the
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> to leave. Basically, the <term
						ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> do not have their own country and only
					engage in self-interest. Lacking patriotism, they are to have any sacrifice for the sake of interest/profit. For the sake of
					Germany, they are merely seeing [our war] to have nothing to do with them; worse, their deep-seated economic power is destroying
					Germany’s <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1049" type="subject">wartime control economy</term>.
				</item>
			</list>
			<p rend="margin noindent">(told by a <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_germans">German</term> named Peistein bound for <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/1850147/tokyo.html">Tokyo</placeName> ) </p>
			<list type="ol" rend="a">
				<item>Although more than two million <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> in
						<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Germany</placeName> like us have faced all
					kinds of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-642" type="subject">persecution</term> by the <term
						ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_germans">German</term>
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1176" type="subject">authorities</term> in recent years, we have
					tried hard to make a living. With the outbreak of the war in Europe, their methods have become more stringent and violent. At
					last, our <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">living</term> is coming under <term
						ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-662" type="subject">threat</term>, and we have reached the point of
					having no choice but to seek <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">refuge</term>
					abroad. Words cannot describe the ways of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-642" type="subject"
						>persecuting us Jews</term>. Under the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-834" type="subject"
						>ration system</term> of life necessities, compared to ordinary <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_germans">Germans</term>, [we
					receive] one fourth of all <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term> except
					bread and one package of 50 cigarette each month. No sweets, alcohol or similar items is given. It is worse when it comes to
					entertainment. We cannot go to the cinema or restaurant because they post <q>No <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> Allowed</q> outside. When
					withdrawing money, we are limited to the amount for purchasing those life necessities and cannot freely access our savings.
				</item>
			</list>
			<p rend="margin hanging">At the personal level, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-642" type="subject"
					>persecution</term> is even more severe. Association with <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> is strictly
				forbidden, and even <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">kids</term> are not allowed to
				play with <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_germans">German</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">kids</term>. Although in legal terms we are not
				expelled from the country, the method used goes against humanity and arouses (uncontrollable) anger. </p>
			<p rend="margin hanging">(told by a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jewish</term>
				merchant named <persName ref="#ehri_dr_Frinkle">Frinkle</persName> bound for <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/1796236/shanghai.html">Shanghai</placeName>)</p>
			<list type="ol" rend="1">
				<item>My Opinion</item>
			</list>
			<p rend="margin noindent">Given the situation described above, there is a need to closely monitor the movement of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> in <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-505" type="subject">transit</term> through our city.</p>
		</body>
